tri-color-dash-light\" },\n          { \"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 21, \"name\": \"Whelen Green L31 Flat Mount Super LED Beacon\", \"url\": \"https://strobesnmore.com/products/whelen-green-l31-flat-mount-super-led-beacon\" },\n          { \"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 22, \"name\": \"Feniex Fusion S 200 Green Lightstick\", \"url\": \"https://strobesnmore.com/products/feniex-fusion-s-200-green-lightstick\" },\n          { \"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 23, \"name\": \"Whelen Green ION Series Super LED Universal Light\", \"url\": \"https://strobesnmore.com/products/whelen-green-ion-series-super-led-universal-light\" },\n          { \"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 24, \"name\": \"Universal UnderCover Screw-In LED Insert Single Light Kit\", \"url\": \"https://strobesnmore.com/products/universal-undercover-screw-in-led-insert-single-light-kit\" },\n          { \"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 25, \"name\": \"ECCO ED3800 Viz™ Series Dual and Tri Color\", \"url\": \"https://strobesnmore.com/products/ecco-ed3800-viz%E2%84%A2-series-dual-and-tri-color\" },\n          { \"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 26, \"name\": \"Whelen Green ION Surface Mount Series Super LED\", \"url\": \"https://strobesnmore.com/products/whelen-green-ion-surface-mount-series-super-led\" },\n          { \"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 27, \"name\": \"Whelen Green 600 Series Super LED Lighthead\", \"url\": \"https://strobesnmore.com/products/whelen-green-600-series-super-led-lighthead\" },\n          { \"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 28, \"name\": \"Whelen Green 700 Series Super LED Lighthead\", \"url\": \"https://strobesnmore.com/products/whelen-green-700-series-super-led-lighthead\" },\n          { \"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 29, \"name\": \"M2 Linear Series Super-LED® SOLO Surface Mount\", \"url\": \"https://strobesnmore.com/products/m2-linear-series-super-led-solo-surface-mount\" },\n          { \"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 30, \"name\": \"Feniex Fusion S 800 Green Lightstick\", \"url\": \"https://strobesnmore.com/products/feniex-fusion-s-800-green-lightstick\" },\n          { \"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 31, \"name\": \"Feniex Fusion S 400 Green Lightstick\", \"url\": \"https://strobesnmore.com/products/feniex-fusion-s-400-green-lightstick\" },\n          { \"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 32, \"name\": \"Feniex Fusion S 100 Green Lightstick\", \"url\": \"https://strobesnmore.com/products/feniex-fusion-s-100-green-lightstick\" }\n        ]\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"FAQPage\",\n      \"@id\": \"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/green-purple-leds#faq\",\n      \"url\": \"https://strobesnmore.com/collections/green-purple-leds\",\n      \"mainEntity\": [\n        {\n          \"@type\": \"Question\",\n          \"name\": \"Why use green LED lights on work trucks or first responder vehicles?\",\n          \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n            \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n            \"text\": \"Green LED lights are commonly run on command vehicles, EMS supervisors, private security details, and utility fleets to signal leadership presence and keep the vehicle visible on an active scene. Because green sits outside the standard red and blue palette, it separates cleanly from surrounding warning lights and helps crews identify the person in charge without extra radio traffic. On both emergency vehicles and privately owned support trucks, that added distinction improves recognition in traffic and low-light conditions.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"@type\": \"Question\",\n          \"name\": \"Are purple LED lights legal on emergency vehicles?\",\n          \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n            \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n            \"text\": \"It depends on your state and vehicle type. In many jurisdictions purple LED lights are permitted for ceremonial roles such as funeral escorts or special-duty vehicles, and some states require a permit or restrict them to specific vehicle classes. Rules for emergency vehicles often differ from the rules for privately owned vehicles, so always confirm your local laws before you install and operate purple warning lights.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"@type\": \"Question\",\n          \"name\": \"What makes green and purple LED lights effective for safety?\",\n          \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n            \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n            \"text\": \"Green and purple are uncommon on the road, so they stand out from typical red, blue, and amber vehicle lighting and draw driver attention faster. That distinction increases the odds other drivers notice the vehicle early and react, which matters most in busy traffic, at roadside scenes, and in low-light or nighttime conditions. Paired with high-intensity output, the color contrast helps both emergency vehicles and POVs stay seen when it counts.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"@type\": \"Question\",\n          \"name\": \"Can these LEDs handle tough work environments?\",\n          \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n            \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n            \"text\": \"Yes. Our green and purple warning lights are weather-sealed and vibration-resistant, with rugged housings built for the demands emergency responders, escort drivers, and fleet operators put on their equipment. Many carry an IP-rated waterproof seal so they hold up to rain, dust, snow, and road shock. Check each product listing for its specific rating and construction details.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"@type\": \"Question\",\n          \"name\": \"Do your LEDs meet industry safety standards?\",\n          \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n            \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n            \"text\": \"Many of our green and purple LED lights are SAE-rated or built to meet NFPA and local emergency-lighting codes, including SAE J595 class ratings on select lightheads. Certifications vary by product, so review each listing for the exact SAE class, compliance details, and beam specifications before you buy to make sure the light fits your role and jurisdiction.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"@type\": \"Question\",\n          \"name\": \"How are purple LED lights used in funeral or escort services?\",\n          \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n            \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n            \"text\": \"Purple LED lights are widely used to mark funeral processions and escort vehicles, where the solemn, uncommon color tells other drivers the group is moving together and should not be split apart. Escort drivers and volunteers often mount purple dash or grille lights on both dedicated units and privately owned vehicles, since the distinct color helps guide and protect the procession in transit while commanding respect on the road.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"@type\": \"Question\",\n          \"name\": \"Can I install green or purple LEDs on my vehicle without rewiring?\",\n          \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n            \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n            \"text\": \"Most of our green and purple lights are plug-and-play or need only minimal wiring, which makes them practical for fleet managers and individual installers alike. Dash and window units are especially quick to set up and transfer between vehicles without drilling, so they are a popular choice for POVs. Our install guides and instructional videos walk through the common setups, and our team can handle a full build when you prefer.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"@type\": \"Question\",\n          \"name\": \"Are your LEDs bright enough for daylight visibility?\",\n          \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n            \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n            \"text\": \"Yes. Our green and purple LED lights use high-lumen output engineered for daylight visibility, so the vehicle stays seen in direct sun as well as at night. Many lightheads add multiple flash patterns to increase conspicuity in bright conditions. Output varies by model, so check each listing for brightness and pattern specifications to match the light to your visibility needs.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"@type\": \"Question\",\n          \"name\": \"Is it legal to mix green or purple lights with other emergency colors?\",\n          \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n            \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n            \"text\": \"This varies by state and vehicle type. Mixing colors is often permitted for command or specialty vehicles, and combinations like purple with amber or white are common on escort and utility setups. Because the rules differ by jurisdiction and by whether the vehicle is an emergency vehicle or a POV, always consult your local regulations before running a multi-color configuration.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"@type\": \"Question\",\n          \"name\": \"Do you offer surface mounts, dash lights, or lightbars in these colors?\",\n          \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n            \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n            \"text\": \"Yes. We carry green and purple LED lights in every major form factor, from discreet hideaway strobes and interior dash and window lights to grille and surface mounts, LED sticks, mini lightbars, and 360-degree beacons. That range lets you outfit an emergency vehicle or a privately owned vehicle with the exact mount your build calls for, in the color your role requires.\"\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n</script>"
